issue_body:
@DJRickyB tracked down a performance regression on a sequence of aggs folks use to visualize logs. The rally configuration looks like this:

```
                "query": {
                  "bool": {
                    "must": [],
                    "filter": [
                      {
                        "match_all": {}
                      },
                      {
                        "range": {
                          "@timestamp": {
                            "gte": "2020-12-14T11:02:06.523Z",
                            "lte": "2020-12-15T11:02:06.523Z",
                            "format": "strict_date_optional_time"
                          }
                        }
                      }
                    ],
                    "should": [],
                    "must_not": []
                  }
                },
                "aggs": {
                  "ad64cabc-0bcf-4c39-ab6c-cedd90396a23": {
                    "terms": {
                      "field": "host.name",
                      "order": {
                        "_count": "desc"
                      },
                      "size": 5
                    },
                    "aggs": {
                      "97997d07-3f9f-424f-bb6d-9c698013e64f": {
                        "date_histogram": {
                          "field": "@timestamp",
                          "fixed_interval": "30m",
                          "time_zone": "UTC"
                        }
                      }
                    }
                  }
                }
```


It looks like #74260 slowed it down significantly. I'd test things like this locally when implementing #74260 and didn't see a regression, but the performance testing infrastructure is a lot better at tracking this sort of thing. I'll pick this up soon-ish. Probably not for a few days, but I would like to at least understand it more closely.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/215970/126355069-bef2e99e-b91f-4a33-a64c-8abce17c001d.png)

We aren't going to revert #74260 because it is more important not to make complex queries much, much worse. But it is a real shame to have hit the 90% case as hard as we did. I don't imagine we'll have a fix for this regression in 7.14 either, sadly.

commit_message:
Improve performance of date_histogram sometimes (#83751)

When the top level query is a boolean like:

```
                "query": {
                  "bool": {
                    "must": [],
                    "filter": [
                      {
                        "match_all": {}
                      },
                      {
                        "range": {
                          "@timestamp": {
                            "gte": "2020-12-14T11:02:06.523Z",
                            "lte": "2020-12-15T11:02:06.523Z",
                            "format": "strict_date_optional_time"
                          }
                        }
                      }
                    ],
                    "should": [],
                    "must_not": []
                  }
                },
```

Our filter-by-filter optimization mistakenly didn't kick in even when
it'd be faster. Convinces it to kick in which should speed things up.

Closes #75542 Closes #82384

